People avoided going to public places for shopping or dining, as they could get all of this done online. 
Businesses were reopening cautiously, and many non-essential workers were planning to work from home for as long as possible. 
Movies were being released directly on Amazon and Netflix instead of in theaters. 
Even social and family gatherings took a new twist with virtual meetings held on Facebook and Zoom. 
For years, Kesav had shunned requests to build a website or do anything online. 
Now, he had abruptly come to face his day of reckoning. 
He had to think long and hard about pivoting his wedding planning business. 
How could he stay relevant at a time when people were shunning large gatherings, parties and events?